mentation</a> up and running.</p>\n<p>Ash and his team of savvy WordPress developers helped us get our new documentation site up and running earlier this year. His team helped us by filtering through old documentation and removing outdated pages, they helped us by writing a ton of new documentation, they guided us through choosing a suitable theme, and they helped pick all the Plugins that are running on the site now. It was a massive undertaking for which the entire WP e-Commerce community is grateful.</p>\n<p>Ash runs a really tight ship in SA and I am totally in awe of his energy, his passion for WordPress and for being a great team leader. We would have no problem recommending LS to anybody that needs custom WordPress development work.</p>\n<p>I also would like to thank Michelle, Cameron, Denise, and Tracey who have also contributed greatly to the developer documentation and the new theme related docs.</p>\n<p>You can find the new docs online at <a href="http://docs.getshopped.org/" target="_blank">docs.getshopped.org</a>, please let us know what you think, in the new year we will spend some more time on the design / UI, and of course we will continue to churn out new content from now until the end of time. If you think we are missing something specific (i.e. a piece of dev documentation / or a theme tutorial) please lets us know here and we&#8217;ll look at adding it to the new years list of things to write.</p>\n<p>Have a great christmas folks, especially The team at Light Speed Dev, who hopefully will have me back next year to talk about <a title="WordPress Game Creator " href="http://www.gamefroot.com" target="_blank">WordPress and Games</a>!</p>\n<p>-Dan</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:121:"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/new-docs-getshopped-org-are-up-and-running-helped-made-possible-by-l