elease the fixes as soon as possible. As a result, a bug sneaked in and broke the Customer Account page. This affected sites that have upgraded to [...]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Gary Cao";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2227:"<p>Hi everyone,</p>\n<p>First of all, we&#8217;re very sorry for hastily pushing out a buggy release yesterday (3.8.7.3). The security issues were quite serious so we were pressured to release the fixes as soon as possible. As a result, a bug sneaked in and broke the Customer Account page. This affected sites that have upgraded to 3.8.7.3. Again we&#8217;re terribly sorry about this mistake and promise to be more careful in future releases.</p>\n<p>Second, the last blog announcement for 3.8.7.3 raised <a href="http://getshopped.org/uncategorized/wp-e-commerce-3-8-7-3-security-release/#comment-8644">some discussion</a> about the way our release announcements should be improved. Thank you for your feedback. We are working on creating a newsletter so that you will receive release announcements directly to your mail box.</p>\n<p>We also realized that saying &#8220;it&#8217;s a security update&#8221; without disclosing any information sort of defeated the purpose of the announcement, and we&#8217;re sorry for that. So here it goes:</p>\n<p>The latest upgrade include fixes for a few potential security issues. These issues affect both 3.7.x and 3.8.x sites. It is <strong>critical that you upgrade your site.</strong></p>\n<p>For sites currently running 3.8.x, you can confidently upgrade your site to 3.8.7.4. You can do that by using automatic update in WordPress, or by <a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/wp-e-commerce/">downloading it from wordpress.org</a>.</p>\n<p>For sites running 3.7.x, <strong>DO NOT</strong> upgrade using WordPress built-in automatic upgrade. Please go to the <a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/wp-e-commerce/download/">Other Version section of our plugin page on wordpress.org</a>, and download 3.7.8.2. Then extract it and upload that version to your wp-content/plugins folder. However, note that we no longer officially support 3.7.x sites. <strong>Active development for bug fixes and new features for 3.7.x has stopped. It&#8217;s highly recommended that the latest 3.8.x version is used to run your shops.</strong></p>\n<p>We can&#8217;t stress this enough: <strong>before upgrading, make sure you have a back up of your files and database, just in case</strong>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:81:"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-7-4-bug-fix-release/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2:"24";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:50:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:38:"WP e-Commerce 3.8.7.3 security release";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:75:"http://getshopped.org/uncategorized/wp-e-commerce-3-8-7-3-security-release/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data"