(208, 1, '2012-01-28 03:00:46', '2012-01-27 19:00:46', '<div class="eight columns">\r\n  <div class="sub-info">\r\n    <p class="sub-info-title">Characteristics:</p>\r\n    <ul class="sub-info-list">\r\n      <li>Very easy application</li>\r\n      <li>Fire rated in both horizontal and vertical joints</li>\r\n      <li>No priming needed for most building/construction joints</li>\r\n      <li>Excellent slump resistance</li>\r\n      <li>Fast cure, tack free within an hour</li>\r\n      <li>Halogen-Free</li>\r\n      <li>Paintable</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="sub-info">\r\n    <p class="sub-info-title">Applications:</p>\r\n    <ul class="sub-info-list">\r\n      <li>Sealing joints, voids and irregular holes</li>\r\n      <li>Maintaining integrity when sealing around pipes and cable penetrations</li>\r\n      <li>Suitable for internal perimeter of fire rated doors, windows and duct systems</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>  \r\n  <div class="sub-info">\r\n    <p class="sub-info-title">Specifications</p>\r\n    <dl class="sub-info-data">\r\n      <dt>Base: </dt><dd>Acrylic emulsion</dd>\r\n      <dt>Curing System: </dt><dd>Physical drying</dd>\r\n      <dt>Skin formation (20°C / 65% R.H.) :</dt><dd>20 minutes</dd>\r\n      <dt>Tack free time :</dt><dd>60 minutes </dd>      \r\n      <dt>Specific Gravity (DIN 53479) :</dt><dd>1.60 - 1.64 g/ml </dd>      \r\n      <dt>Maximum allowed Distortion :</dt><dd>12.5% </dd>      \r\n    </dl>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="sub-info">\r\n    <p class="sub-info-title">Packaging</p>\r\n    <ul class="sub-info-list">\r\n      <li>Volume: 300mL cartridge </li>\r\n      <li>Packaging: 20 cartridges/box</li> \r\n      <li>Standard color: grey, white</li>     \r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>', 'Pereseal FR Intumescent Acrylic Sealant', 'Pereseal ® FR Intumescent Acrylic Sealant is a one component, fire rated joint sealant forming a firm yet flexible seal to join variety of fire rated applications. Non combustible when expo